# UIEventSystem

## Purpose
Performs hit-testing each frame. For every enabled UI entity, computes its world-space bounding
box via recursive parent-chain traversal, then checks the current mouse position against it.
Emits one-frame hover, click, and release events on matching entities. Each event carries the
UUID of the hit entity so downstream systems can identify which element was interacted with
without holding an entt::entity handle.

Guards on InputStateSingletonComponent and RendererConfigSingletonComponent presence; returns
immediately if either is absent.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read |
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| BaseComponent | read |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when mouse position is inside the entity's world-space bounds |
| UIOnClickOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when left mouse button is pressed while hovering |
| UIOnReleaseOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when left mouse button is released while hovering; mutually exclusive with click per frame |
